Last updated: 2025-12-29

1. General Information

Protecting personal data is important to the app owner.
This App is a private, internal tool and is not offered to the public.

2. Data Collected

The App only processes data provided by TikTok, including:

TikTok User ID

Access and refresh tokens

Basic profile information (e.g. username)

Video files and metadata intended for publishing

3. Purpose of Data Processing

Collected data is used exclusively to:

authenticate the TikTok account

publish content via the TikTok API

maintain an authorized connection to the TikTok account

4. Data Storage

Tokens are stored locally or server-side only

No data is sold or shared with third parties

No analytics, tracking, or advertising tools are used

5. Data Sharing

Personal data is not shared with third parties, except:

where technically required to interact with the TikTok API

or where legally required

6. Data Deletion

Authorized data can be removed at any time by:

revoking the Appâ€™s access within the TikTok account settings

deleting locally or server-stored credentials

7. User Rights

As this App is used exclusively by the app owner, no additional user data rights apply.

8. Changes to This Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated if technical or legal requirements change.

9. Contact

For privacy-related questions, the app owner can be contacted via the associated GitHub repository.
